{"Title": "Be Prepared: The EMV Preplay Attack", "Year": 2015, "Source": "IEEE Secur. Privacy", "Volume": "13", "Issue": 2, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 56, "PageEnd": 64, "CitedBy": 8, "DOI": "10.1109/MSP.2015.24", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84928105872&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2003-2012 IEEE.The leading system for smart card-based payments worldwide, EMV (which stands for Europay, MasterCard, and Visa), is widely deployed in Europe and is starting to be introduced in the US as well. Despite this wide deployment, a series of significant vulnerabilities make EMV vulnerable to the preplay attack. Specifically, weak and defective random number generators and various protocol failures leave the system open to fraud at scale.", "AuthorKeywords": ["chip and PIN", "EMV", "payment systems", "POS", "privacy", "random number generators", "security", "security protocols", "smart card"], "IndexKeywords": ["Chip and PIN", "EMV", "Payment systems", "POS", "Random number generators", "security", "Security protocols"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-84928105872", "SubjectAreas": [["Computer Networks and Communications", "COMP", "1705"], ["Electrical and Electronic Engineering", "ENGI", "2208"], ["Law", "SOCI", "3308"]], "AuthorData": {"57220665635": {"Name": "Bond M.", "AuthorID": "57220665635", "AffiliationID": "60031101", "AffiliationName": "University of Cambridge"}, "8880392000": {"Name": "Skorobogatov S.", "AuthorID": "8880392000", "AffiliationID": "60031101", "AffiliationName": "University of Cambridge"}, "56431276600": {"Name": "Anderson R.", "AuthorID": "56431276600", "AffiliationID": "60031101", "AffiliationName": "University of Cambridge"}, "35112989000": {"Name": "Choudary M.O.", "AuthorID": "35112989000", "AffiliationID": "60003161", "AffiliationName": "University Politehnica Bucharest"}, "22433357400": {"Name": "Murdoch S.J.", "AuthorID": "22433357400", "Affi